summary.name: Penguin Characteristics
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about different penguin species, their physical characteristics, and the islands they inhabit.

properties.description: The island where the penguin was observed.
The length of the penguin's beak in millimeters.
The depth of the penguin's beak in millimeters.
The length of the penguin's flipper in millimeters.
The body mass of the penguin in grams.

goals.question: What is the distribution of body mass among different penguin species?
goals.visualization: box plot of body mass by species
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify if there are any significant differences in body mass between different penguin species.

goals.question: How does the beak length vary with respect to the penguin's sex?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of beak length by sex
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify if there are any significant differences in beak length between male and female penguins.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flipper length and body mass?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of flipper length by body mass
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify if there is any correlation between flipper length and body mass among penguins.

goals.question: What is the distribution of beak depth among different penguin species?
goals.visualization: box plot of beak depth by species
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify if there are any significant differences in beak depth between different penguin species.

goals.question: How does the body mass vary with respect to the penguin's island of origin?
goals.visualization: bar chart of body mass by island
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify if there are any significant differences in body mass between penguins from different islands.

code:
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Body_Mass__g_', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass among different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    chart.legend(title='Species', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('How does the beak length vary with respect to the penguin\'s sex?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Species')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
